\title{fNIRS: Hemodynamic (OpenNIRScap)}
\taxon{device}
\author{monaduck1069}
\date{2026-04-04}
\import{macros}
\tag{fnirs}
\tag{hardware}
\tag{diy}
\tag{open-source}
\meta{modality}{hemodynamic}
\meta{manufacturer}{University of Toronto (Kim et al.)}
\meta{product}{OpenNIRScap}
\meta{channels}{24 detectors + 8 dual-wavelength sources}
\meta{price-diy}{$419 BOM (hand-solder)}
\meta{price-jlcpcb}{$220--$320 (JLCPCB assembly)}
\meta{open-source}{true}
\meta{repo}{https://github.com/tonykim07/fNIRS}
\import{macros}

\p{OpenNIRScap. Open-source, wearable, 24-channel fNIRS cap from the University of Toronto (Kim et al., May 2025). 35 mm source-detector separation for cortical depth sensitivity. Validated hemodynamic response detection during cognitive tasks. Replaces bcf-0012 as the primary open-source fNIRS build target.}

\subtree{\title{Architecture}
\taxon{remark}
\ul{
\li{8 dual-wavelength sources: VSMD66694 (660 nm + 940 nm)}
\li{24 detectors: VBPW34S silicon PIN photodiode + AD8618 quad TIA}
\li{ECU: STM32L476 MCU + 8x TMUX1104 analog MUX + PCA9685 PWM}
\li{Sensor PCBs: 25 mm diameter circular, source + detector on same board}
\li{Triangular sensor sets: 1 source + 1 short-channel det + 2 long-channel det at 35 mm}
\li{Communication: USB (isolated via ADUM4160)}
\li{Power: 1100 mAh LiPo, >5 hr runtime}
\li{SNR: 52.3 dB average}
\li{Sampling: 1 kHz effective (12-bit ADC, multiplexed)}
}}

\subtree{\title{Software}
\taxon{remark}
\p{Flask-SocketIO web GUI with real-time 3D brain mesh visualization (Plotly.js + BrainNet Viewer). Modified Beer-Lambert Law processing via NIRSimple library. Bandpass 0.01--0.5 Hz for cortical hemodynamics. Correlation-based signal improvement for HbO/HbR separation. All open source.}}

\subtree{\title{Build routes}
\taxon{remark}

\subtree{\title{JLCPCB assembles everything (recommended)}
\p{JLCPCB fabricates and populates all PCBs -- 24 sensor modules (photodiodes, LEDs, op-amps, MOSFETs, passives) and 1 ECU (STM32, MUXes, PWM controller, USB isolator). You buy only non-PCB items from Amazon.}


\table{
\tr{\th{Source} \th{What} \th{Cost}}
\tr{\td{JLCPCB} \td{24 sensor PCBs + 1 ECU + 1 STLINK breakout, fully assembled} \td{$150--$250}}
\tr{\td{Amazon} \td{Battery, programmer, cables, PLA, headband, velcro, tape} \td{$72}}
\tr{\td{} \td{Total} \td{$220--$320}}
}

\p{Blocker: repo has Altium .PcbDoc source files only, no exported gerbers or BOM. Must import into KiCad 8 and export production files before ordering.}
}

\subtree{\title{DIY hand-solder}
\p{Order bare PCBs from JLCPCB, buy all components from DigiKey, solder yourself. Paper's official cost: $419.}
}}

